  "body": "### Overview\r\nNow we can put args  and kwargs into brownie run, when we are using brownie console mode ([here in code](https://github.com/iamdefinitelyahuman/brownie/blob/master/brownie/project/scripts.py#L18)), but we can't do it through calling of `brownie run` from shell. Possible it's very useful feature in CI/CD, scripts etc\r\n\r\n* I want to deploy my token in CI/CD with dynamic params (for example address of other contracts, which have deployed earlier in CI/CD). Now I deploy their manually through brownie console.\r\n* I want to run my brownie scripts without interactive mode in docker files.\r\n\r\n### Specification\r\nFor example we can add args and kwargs so:\r\n`brownie run <filename> [<function>] [<args1>] â€¦ [<argsN>] [options] [kwargs]`, where\r\n*` [<args1>] â€¦ [<argsN>]` - is tuple of args\r\n*`[kwars]` - is kwargs, but without reserves keys like `--network`\r\n\r\n### Dependencies\r\nI could not search.\r\n\r\nIf we can do these changes, than I can implement it at the next week.",
